Commands for managing the Frappe background job scheduler.

The scheduler processes background jobs like sending emails,
running scheduled tasks, and other async operations.

Examples:
  weg scheduler status     # Check if scheduler is enabled
  weg scheduler enable     # Enable the scheduler
  weg scheduler disable    # Disable the scheduler

Usage:
  weg scheduler [command]

Available Commands:
  disable     Disable the scheduler
  enable      Enable the scheduler
  jobs        List pending background jobs
  purge       Purge failed background jobs
  status      Check scheduler status

Flags:
  -h, --help   help for scheduler

Global Flags:
  -C, --chdir string              Run as if weg was started in <path>
      --config string             Path to config file (default: auto-detect)
      --debug-categories string   Filter debug output: all,config,state,net,git,fs,exec
      --log-level string          Set log level: quiet, normal, verbose, debug, trace
  -o, --output string             Output format: auto, json, table, plain, quiet (default "auto")
  -q, --quiet                     Suppress non-essential output
  -v, --verbose count             Increase verbosity (-v, -vv, -vvv)
  -y, --yes                       Assume yes for all prompts

Use "weg scheduler [command] --help" for more information about a command.
